## Module Boundaries

### Physical Separation (Recommended for Large Teams)

Each context as separate module/target:

```swift
// Package.swift or Podfile
.target(name: "AuthFeature"),
.target(name: "PaymentsFeature"),
.target(name: "AnalyticsFeature"),
.target(name: "SharedKernel"),
.target(name: "Integration")
```

**Dependency rules:**
- Features can depend on SharedKernel
- Features can depend on Integration
- Features CANNOT depend on other Features
- Integration can depend on multiple Features (it's the glue)

### Logical Separation (Small Teams)

Single module with folder structure:

```
Features/
  ├── Auth/
  ├── Payments/
  └── Analytics/
```

Enforced by:
- Code review
- SwiftLint/ktlint rules
- CI checks for import violations

